node.text:
halo infinite monthly update.. 

  343 will be launching a monthly series of videos on their YouTube channel with details of the development of infinite and in this edition they told us the following:

 - In the past flight more than 1,000,000 different games were played against bots, 2,000,000 weapons training and thousands of Tickets with feedback on the game and its status were uploaded.

 - For the next flight you can expect up to 20% performance improvement on PC.

 - There is a new loading screen in place of the three dots from the last flight

 - They chose games with bots and weapon simulations for two reasons: 1. To accustom players to the infinite Sandbox,
 2. Have a greater number of games played and have more stability on the servers.

 - On the next flight they will keep the Halo support site active after the flight is over

 - The campaign will not have online cooperative and split screen and neither will forge since they consider that they are not ready

 - The campaign cooperative would arrive in season 2 (around March 2022 approx) and the forge in season 3 (June 2022 approx)

 - Joseph Staten is excited about the forge of infinite.

 - According to Joseph Staten they are in the stage of polishing the game.

 - They talk about the challenges that Covid has brought to the development of the game

 - They say that Craig looks better.
